[32m+[m[32m## 🏗️ System Architecture[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## ⚠️ Key Assumptions & Current Limitations[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Assumptions[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Demo Mode**: Provides realistic but synthetic data for testing[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Sim Mode**: AirSim integration uses placeholder adapter until full AirSim client is installed[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Tick-based Simulation**: Time advances in discrete ticks (1 tick ≈ 1-2 seconds of real time)[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Deterministic Behavior**: Demo mode with same seed produces identical results[m
[32m+[m[32m5. **Modular Architecture**: Agents can be developed and tested independently[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Current Limitations[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **AirSim Integration**: Sim mode uses structured contracts but requires actual AirSim installation for full functionality[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Scalability**: Tested with 3-5 drones; larger fleets may require optimization[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Real-time Performance**: Not optimized for sub-second response times[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Persistence**: No database or long-term state storage between runs[m
[32m+[m[32m5. **Error Recovery**: Basic error handling; limited automatic recovery from failures[m
[32m+[m
